msgid "Backup"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/file_management/backup.rst:21
msgid "A backup file is automatically created each time you save your project. To restore a backup file, go to :menuselection:`Menu > Project > Open Backup File`. The **Restore Backup File** dialog window will show you a list of all the backup files for your current project."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/file_management/backup.rst:30
msgid "Restoring a backup file"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/file_management/backup.rst:32
msgid "In case something went wrong (corrupted project file, unwanted change, ...), you can now restore a previous version of the file using this feature. Just select the version you want and click |document-open|\\ :guilabel:`Open`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/file_management/backup.rst:36
msgid "**Kdenlive** keeps up to 20 versions of your project file in the last hour, 20 versions from the current day, 20 versions in the last 7 days and 20 older versions, which should be sufficient to recover from any problem."
msgstr ""

